        <h3>Using the Edition</h3>
        <p>
            The "EditionCrafter" view features a side by side visual of encoded and zonded iiif images of the <i>Akron</i> MS and transcriptions and variants of the corresponding portion of the essay. Readers can switch between the five different encoded versions of the text from the dropdown menu at the top right of the viewer. These versions are:
            Folio # Diplomatic Transcription: A Diplomatic Transcription of the <i>Akron</i> MS, which also includes in its display deleted or altered text present in the <i>Berg</i> Manuscripts housed at the New York Public Library.
            Folio # Nineteenth Century: The Version Published in the periodical publication <i>Nineteenth Century</i>, with all MS, Editor, and Typesetter implemented alterations tracked.
            Folio # Intentions 1891: The 1891 <i>Intentions</i> edition, which tracks changes introduced following its periodical publication in 1889.
            Folio # Intentions 1894:The 1894 <i>Intentions</i> edition, mapping differences between the first and second edition of the collection.
            Folio # Fluid: A Fluid Text Version that compiles all the alterations into a single version
        </p>
